properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 14 at 5:00AM PST until January 14 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Las Vegas NV
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected.

* WHERE...western portion of the Owens Valley.

* WHEN...Through 4 PM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Winds could blow down tree limbs and loft unsecured
objects. A few power outages are possible. Travel along Highway
395 could be difficult due vigorous crosswinds, especially for
high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong west winds may sweep across US
Highway 395, especially near Independence CA.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON
